// Semantic direction:
// dyp_læring builds neural networks as compositions of differentiable tensor operations.
// autograd_kontekst records operations on tensors for automatic differentiation.
// beregningsgraf is the DAG of operations; bakoverpass traverses it in reverse.
// kjede_regel propagates gradients backward: ∂L/∂x = ∂L/∂y * ∂y/∂x.
// vektor_jacobian_produkt efficiently computes backward passes without materializing Jacobians.
// gelu (Gaussian Error Linear Unit) approximates Φ(x)*x for smoother activation.
// silu = x * sigmoid(x); closely related to swish = x * sigmoid(β*x).
// xavier_uniform initializes weights to preserve variance across layers for tanh activations.
// kaiming_uniform is designed for ReLU networks: weights ~ U(-√(6/fan_in), √(6/fan_in)).
// batch_norm normalizes each mini-batch; bn_gamma and bn_beta are learned scale and shift.
// rms_norm (used in LLaMA) divides by the RMS of the pre-activations, skipping the mean.
// layer_norm normalizes across the feature dimension; more stable for transformers.
// dropout randomly zeros activations at dropout_rate during training for regularization.
// vekt_forfall adds λ||w||² to the loss, penalizing large weights (equivalent to L2).
// residual_blokk adds the input to the output: y = F(x) + x, enabling very deep networks.
// focal_tap down-weights easy examples: FL = -(1-p_t)^γ * log(p_t) for class imbalance.
// ctc_tap enables sequence-to-sequence training without alignment (for speech/OCR).

// Primitive flow:
// fremoverpass: inndata → lag1 → normalisering → aktivisering → dropout → lag2 → tap
// bakoverpass: tap.backward() -> traverser beregningsgraf baklengs
//   for hvert bereg_node: kall grad_fn(upstream_grad) -> akkumuler i tensor_grad
// batch_norm fremover: x_hat = (x - μ_batch) / √(σ²_batch + ε)
//   y = γ * x_hat + β -> bn_gjennomsnitt + bn_varians oppdateres med momentum
// residual: y = F(x, W) + x -> grad: ∂L/∂x = ∂L/∂y * (∂F/∂x + I)
//   gradienter flyter uhindret gjennom skip_connection -> løser vanishing gradient

// This defines deep learning fundamentals: autograd with the chain rule, activations (GELU/SiLU),
// initializations (Xavier/Kaiming), normalization layers (BatchNorm/LayerNorm/RMSNorm),
// dropout regularization, residual connections, and loss functions (focal/CTC/triplet).
